 
Hatim is very fond of Strings,One day He and his friend Kevin were sitting idle So they decided to do something interesting by playing a game.The game goes like this everytime kevin will give a string (which is composed of several English alphabets) to Hatim,Now Hatim has to write a program to identify those alphabets which repeat itself.as Hatim being new to programming He needs your help in doing it.
Note-String may contain both uppercase and lowercase alphabets(a-z and A-Z) 

Input
First line contains one integer T denoting the number of test cases.Each of the next T lines contains a string S

Output
For each of the T test cases print the repeating alphabets in lexicographical order,if there is no such alphabet repeating itself then print -1

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 100
(Length of String)1 ≤ S ≤ 10^6

Example
Input:
2
AbcdaCb
gHjkGhJ
Output:
a b c
g h j
